args:
Using the powers granted by their costumes,
Melsa and Akasha leave the Halidom to track
down the man controlling the undead. With the
aid of their allies, they manage to slip past the
hungry zombie horde.
Zombies encircle the Halidom, but Melsa\nhas a plan to break the sinister siege...
How did a zombie get in your room,\nAkasha?!
I carried it here after it attacked Sarisse.\nI have an extensive battery of experiments\nI am eager to perform on it.
Oh, and I sealed its movement with magic,\nso you needn't fear its bite.
Zombie bites are like the seventh scariest\nthing about everything you just said.\nAre you sure about all this, Melsa?
Yes. They hesitated when they saw my\ncostume—they think I'm one of them.
If I can play the part convincingly enough,\nI should be able to slip through and get to\nthe man who is controlling them.
It's Zombie 101, and this poor fellow here\nis going to be my professor! First, I need\nto master the zombie moan...
Rawr! Grrr! ...Well? How did I do?
More forceful than the last attempt, but I\nfear a certain adorable aspect remains.
These timorous yelps make mockery of the\nlamentations of the dead! Let the despair\nwell up within you! Use your diaphragm!
Yes! Perfect! ...Wait, hang on.\nWhen did THIS guy show up?
We couldn't help but overhear you earlier.
If there's any way we can help,\nplease tell us!
I don't want to just sit here shaking in my\nboots. If we've got a plan, I want in on it.
It's the least we can do after seeing Melsa\nput her neck on the line for us.
Yeah, we're not gonna sit around doing\nnothing while she's fighting for our sake!
Looks like the cavalry's here, Melsa.
Okay, here's how you can help...
Thus, they joined together to prepare as the dying\nlight of the sun gave way to darkest night.
I found a busted weapon and hammered it\nback into working condition. Take it!
It can only be used once. And avoid using\nit at point-blank range—it's too powerful.
I still feel like I should go with you.
Someone has to stay here and keep\nall these people safe, Sarisse.
Yeah, I know, but... Look, just come\nback safe and sound, all right?
(An exemplary performance,\nMelsa. I daresay I have never seen a more\ncompelling zombie.)
(Yeah, that weird priest turned out to be a\nsurprisingly good vocal coach...)\nWHAA?! AKASHA?! Why are YOU here?!
They're on to us! What now?!
Keep those pyroblossoms going up!\nWe need to keep their attention on us!
(It appears the pyrotechnics have the\nzombies' rapt attention.)
(Akasha, what are you doing here?\nAnd HOW are you here?)
(I constructed this costume based on tales\nof vampires and more than a little magical\ntechnology, and it grants me their powers.)
(Their kind are said to take the form of\nmist to hide their presence at night.)
(These raiments sadly won't transmogrify\nme into damp weather, but obscuring me\nfrom observers was a simple matter.)
(So you decided to come back me up?)
(Our quarry is controlling the undead with\na grimoire, so I thought it prudent we bring\nsomeone versed in magic. Now, onward.)
(We finally made it through the castle\ngates, but there are still a ton of zombies.\nGotta stay focused!)
Grrd EEEeeEeveNIiiiing...!\n(Okay, am I seriously making small talk\nwith a zombie right now?)
(How very curious. It seems this one\nretains some small spark of intelligence.)
Oh no! It's drawing the others' attention!\nThey're swarming for the gates!
And we're all out of pyroblossoms!
Good thing I've still got arrows! HRAAAH!
Acting isn't going to get us through\nthis one... Yah! Hah! Hraaah!
This outfit's cloaking effects cannot fool\nso many eyes at once...
This means we're square, lady.\nNow leave these uglies to us and go!
C'mon, you walkin' stick of jerky!\nYou're dealing with me and my bro now!
If you dead idiots are that hungry,\nyou can all eat my FISTS!
They're surrounded! We have to help them!
There is little we can do for them now.\nCome, we must make haste.
They came to your aid knowing full well\nthe fate which awaited them.
Is wasting this chance and making their\nsacrifice for naught not the crueler choice?
I'm so sorry, you two... But thank you.
